HEADWORD: Disbase
<hw>Dis*base"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Debase</er>.]</ety> <def>To debase or degrade.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor you nor your house were so much as spoken of before I
<qex>disbased</qex> myself.</q> <rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

